In this study, BV-2 murine microglial cell line was cultured at 37 ◦ C in Dulbecco’ s modified Eagle’ s medium (DMEM) with 100 U/ml of penicillin, 100 μ g/ml streptomycin and 10% fetal bovine serum. Before test, BV-2 cells were cultured on a 48-well plate at a density of 1.6 × 105 per well for 12 h. Then the microglial cells were washed twice with serum-free DMEM and pretreated with 10 μ M minocycline (
) or 10 μ M the compounds 1–3 , 5 , 7–15 , 17 , 19–20 , 22 , 23 , and 26 for 30 min, and then incubated with LPS (0.1 μg/ml) and the compounds in serum-free DMEM for 24 h. After 24 h, the cell supernatant was collected and the concentration of inflammatory factor NO was investigated by the Griess method (
) following the instruction. And the effects of the compounds on BV-2 cell viability were detected by the CCK-8 assay (
). The absorbance at 450 nm was read at 0.5 h after adding CCK-8 reagent into the culture medium.
